title: EPA Water Sampling Data April 30th
name: EPA Water Sampling Data April 30th
description:
EPAâ€™s most recent water sampling results collected on April 30th, 2010 from three locations southeast of Venice, LA did not reveal elevated levels of chemicals usually found in oil. These results indicate that water quality for human health and aquatic life are similar to historical data collected in the area.

EPA, in partnership with states, oversees the National Coastal Condition Assessment (NCCA), which is a national coastal monitoring program. EPA is comparing data collected from the BP spill response to historical data from the NCCA.
